1️⃣ git init

Meaning: Start Git tracking in a folder.

Plain English:
👉 “This folder is now a Git project. Start tracking changes.”

Example:

git init
2️⃣ git clone

Meaning: Download a repository from GitHub to your system.

Plain English:
👉 “Copy the project from GitHub to my computer.”

Example:

git clone https://github.com/user/project.git
3️⃣ git status

Meaning: Show what changes are happening in the project.

Plain English:
👉 “Tell me what files changed and what Git sees.”

Example:

git status

It shows:

new files

modified files

files ready to commit

4️⃣ git add

Meaning: Tell Git which files you want to save.

Plain English:
👉 “Prepare these files to be saved.”

Example:

git add file.txt

Add everything:

git add .
5️⃣ git commit

Meaning: Save your changes in Git history.

Plain English:
👉 “Save a version of my project.”

Example:

git commit -m "fixed login bug"
6️⃣ git log

Meaning: Show previous saves (commits).

Plain English:
👉 “Show me the history of changes.”

Example:

git log

Short version:

git log --oneline
7️⃣ git branch

Meaning: Show or create branches.

Plain English:
👉 “Show different versions of my project.”

Example:

git branch

Create new branch:

git branch dev
8️⃣ git checkout

Meaning: Switch to another branch.

Plain English:
👉 “Move to another version of the project.”

Example:

git checkout dev

Create + switch:

git checkout -b feature-login
9️⃣ git push

Meaning: Upload your changes to GitHub.

Plain English:
👉 “Send my code from my computer to GitHub.”

Example:

git push origin main
🔟 git pull

Meaning: Download latest code from GitHub.

Plain English:
👉 “Get the newest changes from GitHub.”

Example:

git pull origin main
1️⃣1️⃣ git fetch

Meaning: Check updates from GitHub but don’t apply them yet.

Plain English:
👉 “Download updates but don’t merge them yet.”

Example:

git fetch
1️⃣2️⃣ git merge

Meaning: Combine two branches.

Plain English:
👉 “Take changes from another branch and add them to this branch.”

Example:

git merge dev
1️⃣3️⃣ git stash

Meaning: Temporarily save unfinished work.

Plain English:
👉 “Hold my current changes safely so I can work on something else.”

Example:

git stash

Restore changes:

git stash pop
1️⃣4️⃣ git diff

Meaning: Show what exactly changed in files.

Plain English:
👉 “Show me the difference between old and new code.”

Example:

git diff
1️⃣5️⃣ git reset

Meaning: Undo changes or commits.

Plain English:
👉 “Go back to the previous state.”

Example:

git reset file.txt
🧠 Simple Workflow (How developers really work)

Typical work:

git clone repo
git checkout -b feature
git add .
git commit -m "new feature"
git push origin feature

Meaning:

Download project
Create new branch
Make changes
Save changes
Upload changes
